<paragraph id="E97036DD3F04FF93FF76FC4EFD07FC02" blockId="49.[151,1437,968,1643]" box="[151,743,968,995]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Size. Maximum size 
<quantity id="2E379B383F04FF93FE65FC4EFE5BFC02" box="[388,443,968,995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
total length (Miller 1986).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F04FF93FF26FC6AFB6FF98A" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F04FF93FF26FC6AFCC6FB5A" blockId="49.[151,1437,968,1643]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Morphology. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FE81FC6AFD26FBE7" bold="true" box="[352,710,1004,1030]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">D VI + I,8–9; A I,8–9; P 17–18</emphasis>
(Miller 1986). Moderately small goby with subcylindrical body, laterally compressed towards caudal fin, head slightly depressed and moderately large. Snout large, gently sloping. Eyes large. Mouth superior, oblique, tip of lower jaw at the horizontal level of eye. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FBA2FBB2FECEFB93" bold="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Angle of jaws below anterior half of orbit.</emphasis>
Predorsal area and nape scaled. Caudal peduncle slender, lower than body depth. The first dorsal fin higher than the second, but with no elongated spines, except in adult males where the second spine is elongated and filamentous (Miller 1986). Caudal fin rounded to truncate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F04FF93FF26FB42FD26FA56" blockId="49.[151,1437,968,1643]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Live coloration. Body mainly brown or beige dorsally with 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FCB6FB42FD2CFAE3" bold="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">5 pale dorsal saddles, faint with no black outlines, each terminating with a midlateral dark blotch</emphasis>
. These midlateral dark blotches of irregular shape, less than 1/3 of body height (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F04FF93FEAEFA8AFE45FAC6" box="[335,421,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1604,1628]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetId="figure-22@50.[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 52. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Deltentosteus quadrimaculatus.A) Photo by R. Pillon, Maddalena, Sardinia, Italy. B) Male with enlarged, pointed first dorsal fin, photo by L. Bérenger, Cagnes-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601731/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FE5BFA8AFDA4FAAB" bold="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Caudal-fin base mark T-shaped and higher than other midlateral marks, covering about entire caudal peduncle height</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F04FF93FDB2FAB6FD47FAAA" box="[595,679,1328,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1604,1628]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetId="figure-22@50.[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 52. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Deltentosteus quadrimaculatus.A) Photo by R. Pillon, Maddalena, Sardinia, Italy. B) Male with enlarged, pointed first dorsal fin, photo by L. Bérenger, Cagnes-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601731/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). Ventral half of body whitish. Females may display a pale blue dot on nape just behind eyes, partly circled in brown. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FD5FFAD2FEC1FA73" bold="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">The first dorsal fin with a black spot distally between fifth and sixth spines</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F04FF93FED0FAFEFE71FA72" box="[305,401,1400,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1604,1628]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetId="figure-22@50.[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 52. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Deltentosteus quadrimaculatus.A) Photo by R. Pillon, Maddalena, Sardinia, Italy. B) Male with enlarged, pointed first dorsal fin, photo by L. Bérenger, Cagnes-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601731/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 52a</figureCitation>
), and with three pronounced dark streaks along first dorsal spine in males (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F04FF93FB3CFAFEFADDFA72" box="[1245,1341,1400,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1604,1628]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetId="figure-22@50.[164,1423,181,1580]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 52. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Deltentosteus quadrimaculatus.A) Photo by R. Pillon, Maddalena, Sardinia, Italy. B) Male with enlarged, pointed first dorsal fin, photo by L. Bérenger, Cagnes-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601731/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 52b</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F04FF93FAB5FAFEFEA1FA57" author="Miller, P. J. &amp; Loates, M. J." pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref61875" refString="Miller, P. J. &amp; Loates, M. J. (1997) Pocket guide to fish of Britain and Europe. HarperCollins Publishers, London, 288 pp." type="book" year="1997">Miller &amp; Loates 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F04FF93FEADFA1AFE3CFA56" author="Louisy, P." box="[332,476,1436,1463]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F04FF93FE09FA1AFD5AFA56" author="Pillon, R. &amp; Delcroix, J. &amp; Berenger, L." box="[488,698,1436,1463]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref63072" refString="Pillon, R., Delcroix, J. &amp; Berenger, L. (2016 a) Signalisation de / Record of Deltentosteus quadrimaculatus, 25 April 2016 (obs. 18 June 2013, photo  1979). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 28 September 2021)" type="url" year="2016">
Pillon 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FDD3FA1BFD83FA57" box="[562,611,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2016a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F04FF93FF26FA46FAFBFA3A" blockId="49.[151,1437,968,1643]" box="[199,1307,1472,1499]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
