<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F04FF93FB7DFA47FAF4FA3B" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1770" box="[1180,1300,1473,1499]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FB7DFA47FB4DFA3B" box="[1180,1197,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FB5AFA47FAF4FA3B" box="[1211,1300,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F04FF93FF26FA62FD5CF9C3" blockId="49.[151,1437,968,1643]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Habitat. Infralittoral to circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F04FF93FCACFA62FC51FA1E" box="[845,945,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="76.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="2.0">2–150 m</quantity>
on soft bottoms, mostly sand, also on mud (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F04FF93FF7EF98EFED0F9C2" author="Louisy, P." box="[159,304,1544,1571]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F04FF93FEDDF98EFDECF9C3" author="Pillon, R. &amp; Delcroix, J. &amp; Berenger, L." box="[316,524,1544,1571]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref63072" refString="Pillon, R., Delcroix, J. &amp; Berenger, L. (2016 a) Signalisation de / Record of Deltentosteus quadrimaculatus, 25 April 2016 (obs. 18 June 2013, photo  1979). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 28 September 2021)" type="url" year="2016">
Pillon 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F04FF93FE67F98FFE57F9C3" box="[390,439,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2016a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F04FF93FDF9F98FFD4FF9C3" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[536,687,1544,1571]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F04FF93FF26F9AAFB6FF98A" blockId="49.[151,1437,968,1643]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Geographic distribution. Mediterranean and adjacent Atlantic Ocean: in the Mediterranean, from 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F04FF93FAD6F9AAFA7CF9A7" box="[1335,1436,1580,1606]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
along northern coast to the Levant; in the Atlantic, from Galicia to 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F04FF93FC65F9D7FC09F98A" box="[900,1001,1617,1643]" name="Morocco" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(Miller 1986).
</paragraph>
